    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Duke University Asks The Right Question</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mamaroneck High counselor Bob Sweeney letter on September 24 article on private college counselors praises Duke Univesity for asking what help applicants have received on their college essays (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I salute Duke University for asking what help the applicant has received in writing their college essay.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I salute Duke University for asking what help the applicant has received in writing their college essay.</p>
        <p>Duke and the highly selective colleges are looking for independent, self-reliant, honest, creative, thoughtful, confident, organized and resourceful students who can write well and think on their feet. I am not so sure these students will be discovered in the offices of independent counselors who are helping them with their essay and packaging them to ''make you look the way you would on the best day of your life.''</p>
        <p>BOB SWEENEY  Ossining</p>
        <p>The writer is a school counselor at Mamaroneck High School.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
